{"version":1,"entries":{"person_37034_translations":{"at":1772689422194,"data":{"id":37034,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"DE","iso_639_1":"de","name":"Deutsch","english_name":"German","data":{"biography":"Rick Kavanian, geboren als Richard Horatio Kavanian am 26. Januar 1971 in München, ist ein deutscher Schauspieler, Komiker, Autor und Synchronsprecher. Er wuchs in einer armenischen Familie auf, die aus Bukarest nach München emigrierte.  Seine Zusammenarbeit mit Michael Herbig begann 1990 bei einer Radioshow und führte zu zahlreichen erfolgreichen Filmkomödien und Parodien, wie \"Der Schuh des Manitu\" und \"Traumschiff Surprise – Periode 1\".\n\nRick ist auch als Synchronsprecher bekannt und hat unter anderem die deutschen Stimmen für Austin Powers und Marty aus \"Madagascar\" geliehen.","name":"Rick Kavanian","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"","name":"Rick Kavanian","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CH","iso_639_1":"de","name":"Deutsch","english_name":"German","data":{"biography":"","name":"Rick Kavanian","primary":false}}]}},"person_5614144_translations":{"at":1772689438308,"data":{"id":5614144,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"","name":"Mat Hill","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"RU","iso_639_1":"ru","name":"Pусский","english_name":"Russian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Мат Хилл","primary":false}}]}},"person_13283_translations":{"at":1772689440088,"data":{"id":13283,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"SE","iso_639_1":"sv","name":"svenska","english_name":"Swedish","data":{"biography":"","name":"","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Old good \"Emo-chan\" of modern Japanese cinema. Emo's father was a close friend of legendary episode player Taji Tonoyama in elementary school days. His mother's grandfather ran a shamisen store in Ginza, Tokyo. Both parents like movies and theaters. After graduating from Machinery Department of Tokyo Industrial High School, Emoto got a job at a trading company. However, he became an actor and became a student of the acting classes of the theater company \"Marui\", which is headed by Nobuo Kaneko, and met Yusaku Matsuda who was in the same class.  In 1999, he won the Japanese Academy Award for Best Actor for his performance in Dr. Akagi. He also won the award for best supporting actor at the 7th Hochi Film Award for Dotonbori River and Hearts and Flowers for Tora-san.","name":"Akira Emoto","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"KR","iso_639_1":"ko","name":"한국어/조선말","english_name":"Korean","data":{"biography":"","name":"에모토 아키라","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"柄本明（日语：柄本 明／えもと あきら Emoto Akira，1948年11月3日—），日本知名男演员，东京都出身，曾获得多座日本电影奖项。身高175cm，血型B。\n\n柄本明28岁时，加入剧团“东京干电池”，并以喜剧演员而受到注目，连续参与舞台剧《蒲田进行曲》、电影《水手服与机关枪》、《寅次郎的故事》等知名戏剧的演出而获得人气。1998年，以电影《肝脏大夫》获得日本电影金像奖最佳男主角奖。2003年，再度以《花》、《ドッペルゲンガー》和《盲侠》中的演技获得每日电影奖最佳男配角奖。1992年，初执导电影《空がこんなに青いわけがない》。2010年，以电影《恶人》中的被害者父亲一角获得日本电影金像奖最佳男配角奖。2011年，获日本政府颁发紫绶褒章，以表彰柄本明在戏剧艺术上的贡献。\n\n妻子为已故女演员角替和枝（1954年-2018年10月27日），两人育有一女二子。两个儿子柄本佑和柄本时生皆为演员。大女儿亦是电影幕后工作者。","name":"柄本明","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"PL","iso_639_1":"pl","name":"Polski","english_name":"Polish","data":{"biography":"","name":"","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"RU","iso_639_1":"ru","name":"Pусский","english_name":"Russian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Акира Эмото","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"JP","iso_639_1":"ja","name":"日本語","english_name":"Japanese","data":{"biography":"","name":"柄本明","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"CZ","iso_639_1":"cs","name":"Český","english_name":"Czech","data":{"biography":"","name":"Akira Emoto","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"DE","iso_639_1":"de","name":"Deutsch","english_name":"German","data":{"biography":"","name":"Akira Emoto","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"FR","iso_639_1":"fr","name":"Français","english_name":"French","data":{"biography":"","name":"Akira Emoto","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"IT","iso_639_1":"it","name":"Italiano","english_name":"Italian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Akira Emoto","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"ES","iso_639_1":"ca","name":"Català","english_name":"Catalan","data":{"biography":"","name":"Akira Emoto","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"HK","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"從高中畢業後，柄本明進入普通商社工作，然而有志於演藝事業的他不久後便辭職成了一名自由演員，不斷出入各種劇場尋找機會。1977 年，柄本明和一些志同道合的朋友組成了劇團《東京乾電池》，開始在小型劇場活躍。不久後，柄本明在富士電視台的節目《該哈哈大笑了》中擔任時事評論主持人，由此成了全國知名的藝人。\n\n同時，柄本明還不斷出演電影，其中包括一些名片，比如：《水手服和機關槍》（1981、相米慎二）、《穿越天城》（1983、三村晴彥）、《電影天地》（1986、山田洋次）、《木村家的人們》（1988、瀧田洋二郎）、《北京的西瓜》（1989、大林宣彥）等。從八十年代末開始，柄本明進一步涉足電視劇，出演了大量作品，其中有 TBS 的《參差不齊的蘋果們 2》、NHK 的《太平記》等等。1993 年，柄本明推出了自己執導的電影《天並不那麼藍》。從九十年代後半期開始，柄本明佳作不斷，他在《談談情、跳跳舞》（1996、周防正行）、《身心投入》（1997、荒井晴彥）、《鰻魚》（1997、今村昌平）等片中的出演都受到了廣泛好評。1998 年，柄本明主演了電影《肝臟大夫》，他憑藉此片獲得了報知電影獎和日本學院獎的最佳男主角獎。2004 年，他又憑藉在《盲俠座頭市》中的精彩表演贏得了每日電影評選的最佳男配角獎。2009 年，柄本明頂住右翼壓力出演《拉貝日記》，扮演南京大屠殺主犯松井石根。柄本明一直孜孜不倦地耕耘在演藝園地中，他演技紮實，往往能夠抓住人物特點，傳神地展現出人物的魅力。","name":"柄本明","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"UA","iso_639_1":"uk","name":"Український","english_name":"Ukrainian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Акіра Емото","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"BR","iso_639_1":"pt","name":"Português","english_name":"Portuguese","data":{"biography":"","name":"Akira Emoto","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"SA","iso_639_1":"ar","name":"العربية","english_name":"Arabic","data":{"biography":"","name":"آکیرا اموتو","primary":false}}]}},"person_3834195_translations":{"at":1772689441223,"data":{"id":3834195,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Hayashi Yuta is a Japanese actor.","name":"Yuta Hayashi","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"JP","iso_639_1":"ja","name":"日本語","english_name":"Japanese","data":{"biography":"","name":"林裕太","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"CZ"